}{}${R}_t$\end{document} reduced from 4.86 to 4.5 and then to 4.29 in the third week. Figure 1 illustrated the decline of the effective reproduction number over time as increasingly nonpharmaceutical interventions. The effective reproduction number further decreased to 2.37 between 6 March 2020 and 3 April 2020, most likely due to increasingly stringent measures for social distancing, and ‘stay at home’ policies, but also the enforcement of quarantine of household and other contacts of confirmed cases.
